description.$t: Rambler lost his leg after having been shot but that hasn't stopped him from being a playful affectionate guy. He can play a little rough so he would be best in a home with no kids. As well an experienced dog owner with large dog experience would be best. Now Rambler isn't a dog to take jogging or for long walks but he does have a lot of love and affection to give. Rambler has had a rough time but with the right family he could make a great companion. He is looking for the loving home he is so deserving of.

Annie is an affectionate, friendly 4 year old girl who jumps up excitedly to meet new people. She is good with other dogs and loves being patted. It is amazing how much love she has for people considering everything she has been through. You see Annie is a survivor of the horrific dog meat trade in Asia. Rescued from what had been a barbaric death she was taken to a shelter in northern Thailand which is home to 1200 other rescued dogs as well. It was there that her personality was apparent to the Soi Dog staff who every month travel to this northern shelter to assess and bring back a group of dogs to their main facility in Phuket. In Phuket they further assess the dogs, work with them and fully vet them which includes spaying, vaccinating, micro chipping and any other vetting necessary. Annie is now ready to begin her new life in a loving home in Canada. At under 40 pounds this sweet girl is a good fit for almost any household. If you'd like to adopt Annie and give her the loving home she is so deserving of please email firefighterdogrescue@gmail.com  Adoption fee is $400

Just a few months ago Alice and her sister Tiara were found in a cage in Thailand nearly starved to death. I do have pictures of how they looked at the time but they are disturbing. It is amazing how far these two sweet girls have already come in such a short time. Sure they still look a little rough but in a couple more months you won't be able to tell the horrors they have gone through. And only a dog could be abused so much and yet still show so much love like Alice and Tiara do. Alice and Tiara will be soon fully recovered and ready for their new lives in a loving home in Canada. We would like to adopt them out to the same home as they are somewhat bonded but individual adopters will be considered. If you are interested in adopting Alice or both her and Tiara please email firefighterdogrescue@gmail.com  Adoption fee for Alice is $400 or $500 for the pair. For more information phone 416-303-3085 or check out Alice and Tiara Need A Home on Facebook

Meet Sadie who is 6 and her son Bricks 4 both spayed and neutered looking for a home together. They are extremely affectionate and listen well. These 2 dogs are very affectionate and thrive for human contact. When I do visit them I bring them treats and spend time with them. It breaks my heart when I leave.  Bricks was attacked when he was a puppy so does not like other dogs.  They are both great in the car. Sadie is a German Shepherd and her son is a labx. They cannot be separated as they love each other and have been together for their whole lives.These 2 dogs are very healthy and can keep going to my vet for future visits if needed. We will cover the costs. Our vet is in Pickering.

They are presently at a business being neglected and need to get out of their as soon as possible. Winters  and summers are terrible for they do not have the proper set up and the owner will not fix.  They are great off leash and listen well. They do get food and water when one worker goes in but if he doesn't they do not eat. The weekends are the worst because their is no one there Please call 647-929-1553 if serious. Please tell me about yourself when inquiring. We will supply 5 months of dog food these 2 lovely dogs.. A home visit is a prerequisite for adoption.  We will also be asking for a reference from your vet. An adoption fee will be charged.

We are always in need of people who are willing to foster our dogs until we can find permanent homes.

Meet Bricks 4 year old lab mix very friendly along with her mom Sadie 6 year old german shepherd, they need a home together. Both these dogs are so affectionate and want attention but they are just ignored where they are. Its heartbreaking when  I visit them and bring them treats and spend time with them.  They need a loving home where they can be spoiled.   These 2 dogs are very friendly and are great off leash and listen well. Bricks was attacked at a puppy by another dog so he is not dog friendly.  They are presently at a business and they are no longer wanted. They do not have a proper set up for the year round  elements and need to be rehomed for the owner does not want to fix. 

They are both spayed and neutered, and are great in the car.  They love each other and we will supply 5 months of dog food for these 2.  They will have to be housetrained  and need a yard to run and play. We are willing to pay for future visits to our vet if needed, our vet is in Pickering.   Please call 647-929-1553 if interested. We are always looking for fosters also. They are both very healthy.A home visit is a prerequisite for adoption.  We will also be asking for a reference from your vet. An adoption fee will be charged.

We are always in need of people who are willing to foster our dogs until we can find permanent homes....

Very affectionate, sweet, gentle, loves to cuddle, and very smart.

Born June 1, 2016 spayed and UTD. Crate trained but can be left alone for a short period of time, she's not destructive, does not jump on people and is very gentle with treats. She's not interactive with other dogs and currently tries to avoid them, but could certainly be trained to socialize. She saw a cat once and froze but she did walk by it

sweet girl FIDDY is looking for her foster/FUREVER home! She's approx 2 yrs old, spayed & just the sweetest pup ever. Walks okay on leash, house trained (but they sometimes have accidents the first few days) she's great with other dogs too! She's believed to be an Irish wolfhound mix!

Nobody has claimed Fiddy as their family member, so she is now ADOPTED: Today on our way back from getting Thunder's xrays, Sharon & I decided to stop at Burger King to get a cold drink before returning to the Veterinarian in Sosua. As we were leaving we saw a dog laying on the sidewalk. We gave her some treats and Sharon decided to move them far away so she would not risk getting run over and the gas attendant told her the dog didnt' belong to anyone, it has been there for over 2 months and they need it out of there. There was a second dog, but it was run over and died :( After some intervention and negotiation with the doorman of Burger King, and the gas attendant, Sharon secured the dog and we promised to try to find its owner and if not then get her adopted out. If this is your dog, or you know the owner of this dog, please message us. She does have a name as it is on her tag, so if you know her, please message me her name and we will get her returned to you. If nobody claims her, she will be for adoption. She is approx 2 yrs old and weighs 50 lbs , she is already spayed and will be UTD on vaccinations. For now her public name is Fiddy ;) Tarah Zandra Motuzas with Sharon Villaman.

Simcoe is an amazing dog with a larger than life personality! She'll chase a ball with you, follow you through the woods and then snuggle up nice and close on the couch. She's a little excited by car rides and it's a good idea to buckle her in. Who can blame her? The car takes you to fun places! 

Simcoe is a 7 year old, energetic, fun, happy, playful dog looking for a forever home. She loves to walk, loves people and loves to play. Simcoe does enjoy playing large, calm dogs, but she can be overwhelming for small dogs. She just doesn't know her own size! We will require a home where Simcoe is the only dog. While she will play outside, she doesn't like to have doggy friends in her home. 

If you would like to meet Simcoe, please email us to start the conversation. Please note that Simcoe is being fostered in the Bowmanville area and you must be able to travel there to meet her. We require that you complete an adoption application prior to meeting any of our dogs. An adoption fee will apply at time of adoption.

Jenny is a beautiful American Bulldog.  She is approximately 3 years old. She is a very energetic girl and is easily motivated. She has a very big heart and is very sweet once she trusts you. She loves to play ball and is a big goofy girl.
Jenny has some social issues and takes a bit to warm up to strangers. With a proper introduction she relaxes quickly. We are working with her on an ongoing basis to recondition her socially.
What we are seeking for Jenny in an adopter is:
-experienced and confident person(s)
-very physically active lifestyle that would include Jenny. 
-someone dedicated to join in on her training sessions and continue working with her
-ability to follow protocols
Jenny is OK with DOGS (with proper intros)
NO kids
NO cats

For an adoption application, please visit our website at www.benevolentbullyrescue.com.  For further info about our organization please also visit our Facebook page at www.facebook.com/benevolentbullyrescue  Please note we do not adopt outside of the Province of Ontario.  Benevolent Bully Rescue's standard adoption fee is $500.00.

Jeffery is a 2 yr old energetic Husky male. Save from a Northern reserve this boy is a shining light of hope and love. He gets along well with all dogs and would do well with older children. 
He will require daily exercise and is learning basic commands. 
He's a sweet caring boy who would love an active family or person to spend his time with. He loves to hit the trails and will follow along with his "pack" 
He is utd with shots, neutered and micro-chipped. 
Our short app can be found at www.ruffstartnewbeginnings.com and we welcome visitors to our Rescue Retreat in Colborne. 
(He does have a prey drive so a home without cats is recommended)

Toula is a lovely gal who would thrive best to someone who is works from home or retired. She craves human attention and likes all other dogs. 
She can be vocal when left alone, but with some confidence building skills and some patients when she arrives to her new home will be key in helping her find her permanent address! 
She is spayed UTD with shots microchipped and is currently on Brevacto *for fleas and ticks.
she is at our Ruff Start New Beginnings retreat in Colborne and we're happy to have visitors by appt only.
our application can be found at www.ruffstartnewbeginnings.com 
ADOPT FEE of $350 applies

Angle is young, full of energy foxhound. She gets along very well with dogs, cats and LOVES people of all ages. *Kids are her favorite! 
She listens well learning basic commands, she's house trained and would love an active family and prefer a dog or cat friend while you are at work or away. 
She is good on a lead and loves to go for a walk.  She will require daily exercise and sleeps through the night. She's quiet and is a huge fan of cuddling up to spend time with her people. 
If you'd like to meet Angle she is here at our rescue retreat in Colborne,
Our app can be found at www.ruffstartnewbeginnings.com and she'd be very glad to meet you.
She is utd with shots, spayed and microchipped.

Malfoy
Male / Neutered / $425
Terrier mix
Age: 1 year old
Weight: 17LBS
Location Bowmanville

Malfoy is a sweet boy, shy and just needs adjustment time with his new family. He doesn't have a mean bone in him, loves to cuddle, belly rubs and enjoy his family. Malfoy is house trained and crate trained.   He plays really well with other dogs. He  doesn't seem to pay much attention to cats. Malfoy has been introduced to a raw diet to get him to eat and he really enjoys his meals now. He needs a quiet home, older kids only as he gets scared of loud noises and doesn't want to be chased. He needs  another dog companion, fenced in yard and someone to just love Him!  This sweet angel would make a great companion and forever friend.

For more info, please email his foster mom at whitepaws@rogers.com , and to fill out an application, visit www.dibsrescue.com

Please keep sharing! Since yesterday, this post reached almost 22k people but we have still not had a single request for an adoption application. :( 

Folks, Hope and Lidia have had very little adoption interest and are UDR's longest case. We need your help by sharing these two girls and finding them a forever home. We realize that finding a home for two dogs is harder than just one but this mother/daughter duo are very bonded and they don't want to be split apart. From an adoption standpoint, they are great company and entertainment for each other. They're the perfect size (45-50lbs) and very little trouble. 

Lidia is a pointer/husky mix and is Hope's mom. Hope's father was a purebred Border Collie. They are both spayed and vaccinated. Lidia is 2.5 and Hope is 1.5 years old. They have been raised with children. Both are housetrained and crate trained and are very intelligent dogs. They are used to country-living and so they need some work on leash manners. A Halti, patience, and consistent one-on-one walks will do them wonders. They live with two cats but do like to chase cats. A home with a fully fenced yard for them to relax in would be great. They love the outdoors. They would prefer to be the only dogs in the home as this is what they've always known and they have had little exposure to other dogs. Two is lots of dog anyway! :) 

Please message us if you can offer these two lovely dogs a forever home. They're located in Guelph, ON.

Meet Rocko!

This looker is a 7 year old Boston Terrier/Boxer cross, fully vetted and neutered. He loves people, kids and other dogs. He's ridiculously affectionate and has been an amazing playmate for his foster sister - but now it's his time to get noticed!

His goofy ways make his foster laugh and we know he would be a great addition to any family. He just wants to be loved and to be with people. He is full of beans and just loves to love life.

Cats are unknown at this point. 

Please send us a message if you'd like to learn more!

Daisy was found as a stray in Miami and was scheduled to be euthanized as she had a terrible skin condition, with open sores and scabs all over a body with almost no hair.  The shelter changed their mind when the medical personnel commented on how sweet and gentle she was.   She was minimally treated for non-contagious demodex mange and has received further treatment since leaving the shelter,  She now has a clean bill of health, and although her hair has not fully grown back she is ready for her new and forever home.  Daisy is estimated to be about 10 - 11 months old, is a high energy pup and could do well living with another calm  but playful dog, as her exuberance is not always welcome.  She is in a foster home with a young puppy and another young male and they play endlessly and then Daisy calms down for cuddling with her family.  She is crate trained, good with children (she loves them but she could knock a young child over), sweet and gentle, microchipped, housebroken, and walks quite well on a front clasping harness. The 4 year old in her foster home loves to lie on the floor and let Daisy lick her and Daisy is happy to oblige.  She would need obedience classes as she has not had much training.  She knows basic commands.  A fenced back yard is a must for Daisy as her recall is not great yet, but she has only been out of the shelter and in an actual home for less than 2 weeks now.  Her microchip is registered to the Miami-Dade shelter so her owner would have to re-register the chip with a Canadian company.  Because Daisy was a stray we are guessing at her breed mix but she seems to be predominantly lab.  She is amazing and so loving with people.   Daisy is friendly sweet and affectionate - a real people dog.

Patsy Cline and 3 of her siblings have come to us all the way from Georgia! We were alerted to them by a friend of ours who travels down for business and knew of these orphan puppies that lost their mom when she was hit by a car.
A good Samaritan took them in and they were living in her garage. 

Now they are here and in our foster care program! She is just over 6 months old, 44 lbs, and will be a big girl once fully grown! The notes below are from her foster mother. 

Pasty enjoys the company of other dogs. She is a nervous lady as she has come from rural Georgia. A home with a fenced in yard for her to romp and play would be best for miss Patsy. 

She is house trained, but will need an adopter that is willing to work on her fear. She bonds quickly to her handler but will need help getting exposed to life here in the GTA.

She is sweet and loving, and is looking for a family to love her and show her how good life can be. 

Please send us a note if you'd like to meet miss Patsy Cline! Our Petfinder site is not working 100% so please email udrc.applications@gmail.com

Drake is a sweet and beautiful boy. He weighs about 50 pounds and is neutered and up to date on her shots. He is three years old and looking for a home to call his own.  He was rescued from Louisiana.  He had some skin allergies in Louisiana and is doing much better now that he is in Toronto and not kept outside and given good food.  He gets along well with other dogs and children. We aren't sure how he is with cats. He loves to go for walks but is calm in the home.  He needs his furever home.  Please contact our rescue Cause4paws Toronto immediately as he needs a home right away - C4PToronto@gmail.com.  Please send your name, town, phone number, and some basic information.  We will get in touch with our application and give you a call to discuss Drake and our foster to adopt program.  Thanks so much for your interest.

Bailey is a 6 year old Labrador mix. Rescued in Romania she was used as a puppy mill dog, Unfortunately she has been diagnosed with late stage lymphoma.  Right now she is doing well.  She takes two pills daily.  She is very sweet and bonded with the puppy she was rescued with.  According to the vet she only has 2 - 6 months to live and we want to see her spoiled and loved during that time.  Our rescue, Cause4Paws Toronto, will cover all costs.  We would like the family that wants to adopt Bella to keep Bailey with her for as long as she has.   We would love to talk to you about Bailey and Bella, send you an application and set up a time to meet them.  Please contact us at c4ptoronto@gmail.com.

Muffy is a sweet girl.  She loves other dogs and people.  She is three years old and has so much love to give.  She weighs about 45 pounds and has a beautiful soft coat.  Muffy is up to date on her shots and has been spayed. She loves to snuggle.  She would be perfect for any home that wants a loving dog.  She is calm but also loves to go for walks and explore.  She has had been in a small rural shelter and would thrive in a loving home.  Please contact our rescue Cause4Paws Toronto for more information.  Our email is c4ptoronto@gmail.com.  We are a small foster based rescue and we would love to find a home for Muffy within an hour of downtown Toronto.  All of our dogs are placed on a trial basis in our foster to adopt program.  We can't wait to see Muffy with her furever family.

Demis is a four year old male.  He gets along well with other dogs.  He adores people. 
 Demis is neutered and up to date on his shots.  He weighs about 40 pounds.  Demis is happy and loves to go on adventures.  He has been in a small rural shelter for too long and desperately needs his own home and love and care and warmth. Please contact our rescue Cause4Paws Toronto for more information.  Our email is c4ptoronto@gmail.com,  We are a small foster based rescue and we would love to find a home for Demis within an hour of downtown Toronto.  All of our dogs are placed on a trial basis in our foster to adopt program.  We want Demis to have his furever family.

Dennis was rescued in Russia with a bad leg injury. He healed very well but he does have a limp.  He is still very fast and active, just limping. He is very sweet and loving, a llittle shy and quiet.  Dennis is four years old, neutered, and up to date on shots.  He weighs about 45 pounds.  Dennis is good with dogs and doesn't bother cats.  He is also good with children.   Dennis has been with his friend Luke in a rural shelter for a couple years and we  would love to see them adopted together if possible.   Please contact our rescue Cause4Paws Toronto for more information.  Our email is c4ptoronto@gmail.com.  We are a small foster based rescue and we would love to find a home for Dennis within an hour of downtown Toronto.  All of our dogs are placed on a trial basis in our foster to adopt program.  We want Dennis to have his furever family.

Bella is an eight month old Spaniel mix. Rescued in Romania she is with a foster with dogs, children, and cats. She is sweet, happy, and playful. She has lots of puppy energy and loves to learn. Our rescue Cause4paws Toronto is looking for a loving home with a fenced in yard and lots of time to spend.  We also would like her to have another dog in the family.  Also she arrived with a dog that may be her mom - Bailey.  Unfortunately when Bailey arrived our vet determined that she has late stage lymphoma.  Our vet estimates that she has about 2 - 6 months.  She takes two pills a day and is doing good.  Our rescue will take care of all medical costs but we would like her to be spoiled and loved and kept with Bella until she passes.   We would love to talk to you about Bella and Bailey.  We can send you an application and set up a time to meet them. Please contact us at c4ptoronto@gmail.com.

Luke is a sweet boy.  He is five years old, neutered and up to date on shots.  He and his friend Dennis are in a small rural shelter and deserve a loving home of their own.  We would love to see them adopted together if possible.  Luke is  neutered, up-to-date with his shots, healthy, friendly,very well behaved, excellent leash manners, knows basic commands.  Please contact our rescue Cause4Paws Toronto for more information.  Our email is c4ptoronto@gmail.com.  We are a small foster based rescue and we would love to find a home for Luke within an hour of downtown Toronto.  All of our dogs are placed on a trial basis in our foster to adopt program.  We want Luke to have his furever family.
